## Evaluation System

> Full details: [docs/evaluation-system.md](docs/evaluation-system.md)

### 10-Point Scale

| Score | Meaning |
|-------|---------|
| 9–10 | Excellent — exceeds requirements |
| 7–8 | Good — meets all requirements (PASS) |
| 5–6 | Acceptable — works but has issues |
| 3–4 | Poor — significant problems |
| 1–2 | Failing — does not meet requirements |

### PASS Criteria
- **Overall weighted score >= 7.5** to proceed to STEP 8
- **No individual category below 7**
- **Security score <= 3 → automatic FAIL** (mandatory rework → STEP 4, cannot be diluted by averaging)

### Evaluation Categories

| Category | Weight | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| Correctness | 30% | Does it work as specified? |
| Code Quality | 20% | Clean, readable, maintainable? |
| Test Coverage | 20% | Are critical paths tested? |
| Security | 15% | No new vulnerabilities introduced? |
| Performance | 15% | No regressions, reasonable efficiency? |

### Output Format (JSON)

```json
{
  "step": 6,
  "issue": "#123",
  "evaluator": "evaluation-ai",
  "scores": {
    "correctness": 8,
    "code_quality": 7,
    "test_coverage": 7,
    "security": 8,
    "performance": 7
  },
  "overall": 7.5,
  "pass": true,
  "comments": "Implementation meets requirements. Minor suggestion: ..."
}
```

