## Repository Boundary Rules

> Full details: [docs/repo-boundary-rules.md](docs/repo-boundary-rules.md)

### Core Rules

1. **Each AI agent operates within its assigned repository only.**
2. **Cross-repo changes require Orchestrator coordination.**
3. **No direct commits from one repo's AI to another repo.**

### Read/Write Permissions

| Agent | Own Repo | Other Repos | Orchestrator Repo |
|-------|----------|-------------|-------------------|
| Developer AI | Read + Write | Read only | Read only |
| Test AI | Read + Write (tests) | Read only | Read only |
| Evaluation AI | Read only | Read only | Read only |
| Orchestrator | Read + Write | Read only* | Read + Write |

*Exception: Orchestrator may make cross-repo config changes when documented.

